cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with resource allocation in cellular networks. It may also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) as it uses utility proportional fairness allocation policy. Additionally, it may belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it presents a distributed resource allocation algorithm. It may also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) as it considers different types of applications with varying QoS requirements. Finally, it may belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it presents a distributed algorithm for resource allocation.
